1.0	"45409.84097222222"	45409.85763888889	"anonymous"		"I agree"	45409.0	"A federal-state program for low-income families that offers bi-monthly or monthly dollars (in the form of a voucher or money card) to purchase food items, with the goal of meeting food as a basic need, reducing hunger/food-deprivation illnesses, and addressing food insecurity."	"Social factors such as housing, transportation, education, etc. that impact health outcomes and shape the distribution and burden of diseases and mortality in different population groups. "	"3"	"3"	"The activity offered real world experience on the decision-making and navigation that goes into trying to plan for meals on a very tight budget in the context of a disease state. A great deal of mental bandwidth was spent just planning for meals, that is, trying to gather coupons or find sales. The budget provided was not sufficient to meet my food needs and I stretched the budget by purchasing a lot of unhealthy food items (canned goods)."	"4"	"4"	"1) Providing community resources for food-insecure patients, 2) Educating patients about healthy food items that they can purchase on a tight budget"	"3"	"Local resources to access and aid in SNAP benefits for patients;"	"4"	"3"	"3"
2.0	"45410.672222222223"	45410.71875	"anonymous"		"I agree"	45410.0	"Food benefits for low income individuals"	"Socioeconomic and environmental factors that influence health"	"4"	"3"	"I had already completed a similar exercise in a previous graduate program so this was not particularly new to me. I would have modified the activity by asking students not necessarily to complete the challenges themselves with these constraints, but to complete a weekly/monthly budget for food allowance and consider how they would utilize public transportation to get to and from the grocery store and to think about how difficult shopping would be if they were from another country or had low literacy. "	"3"	"3"	"This is something that I try to be more conscious of when asking patients about their diet, particularly if they are socioeconomically disadvantaged. "	"3"	"Local resources to access and aid in SNAP benefits for patients;"	"4"	"3"	"3"
3.0	"45411.416666666664"	45411.42083333333	"anonymous"		"I agree"	45411.0	"SNAP is a program that provides funding for low income families to have increased access to healthy foods"	"all the factors outside of a hospital that influence patients health"	"4"	"4"	"It forced me to really increase my focus on food, something I had never done before. Often my day had to be planned around it and the limited meals I could have affected other aspects of my heatlh."	"4"	"3"	"I really try to ask about food more often and provide as many resources as I can to assist patients who may need it."	"1"	"Not very familiar right now;"	"4"	"4"	"4"
