9.0	"5/55/2024  2:24:08 PM"	45427.60902777778	"anonymous"		"I agree"	45427.0	"SNAP Benefits are welfare services provided to low-income families that allow them to purchase groceries that their income would not permit. "	"Social Determinants of health are the conditions in which each individual grow, live, learn, and work. These are factors that include access to resources, good education, adequate housing, safety, etc. These SDoH account for about 60-80% of our health outside of direct medical care. "	"4"	"4"	"It opened my eyes to how truly expensive groceries are as well as how limited the selection might be for purchasers. I could not imagine feeding myself solely on this budget, let alone an entire family (amount of SNAP benefits is adjusted to family size). As a future doctor, it makes me think more about how I see the healthy diet component to our recommendations, and how difficult it is to live a healthy life within this budget. Especially if you have a disease like diabetes, hyperlipidemia, or hypertension, it must be particularly difficult to limit your options even more. I can't imagine having these constraints while working a full time job, going to school, and/or while raising children. "	"3"	"3"	"At Akron General, we have a food pantry as well as a pilot program that helps provide lower income patients with food. Knowing the constraints of SNAP, I have recommended these resources in order to provide additional support. "	"1"	"Benefits are decreasing"	"4"	"5"	"4"
10.0	"45427.746527777781"	45427.75208333333	"anonymous"		"I agree"	45427.0	"Federal government program that provides participants with monetary assistance in obtaining access to foods. "	"SDOH encompass variety of factors ranging from financial to housing to education issues. They impact the opportunities that we can have access to in life."	"4"	"3"	"the SNAP exercise provided a realistic exposure to the realities that people/patients face on a daily basis. The exercise made me think about the helplessness and stress that patients go through in trying to navigate different public systems in trying to obtain food for themselves and their families. "	"3"	"3"	"Try to refer them to social worker or provide them with resources"	"1"	"No I wouldn't have had time to research the current state of SNAP benefits"	"4"	"3"	"3"
